{"entries":[{"id":"clarke-rut-1-1","title":"Ruth 1:1–4:20","author":"Adam Clarke (1760–1832)","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":20},"content":"<p><milestone</p>"},{"id":"clarke-rut-3-1","title":"Ruth 3:1","author":"Adam Clarke (1760–1832)","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<p>type=\"x-importer\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"clarke-rut-3-11","title":"Ruth 3:11","author":"Adam Clarke (1760–1832)","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":11,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":11},"content":"<p>type=\"x-importer\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"clarke-rut-3-18","title":"Ruth 3:18","author":"Adam Clarke (1760–1832)","reference":{"book":"RUT","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":18,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":18},"content":"<p>Verse 3 But now thou art worth ten thousand of us - The particle יתה attah, now, is doubtless a mistake for the pronoun אתה attah, thou; and so it appears to have been read by the Septuagint, the Vulgate, and the Chaldee, and by two of Kennicott's and De Rossi's MSS.</p>"}]}